    "method": "microbial fermentation",
    "description": "Commercially produced by fermentation of glucose or sucrose using the black mold Aspergillus niger. This method replaced extraction from citrus fruits in the early 20th century. Over 2 million tonnes are produced annually, making it one of the most widely manufactured food additives in the world."
  },
