  "fun_facts": [
    "Citric acid is present in every lemon - a single lemon contains about 3 grams of citric acid",
    "It is the most widely used acidulant in the food industry, with over 2 million tonnes produced annually",
    "Produced by fermenting sugar with Aspergillus niger mold, the same process developed in 1917 by James Currie",
    "Citric acid is part of the Krebs cycle (citric acid cycle), a fundamental metabolic pathway in all living organisms",
    "In soft drinks, it provides not just sourness but also helps preserve flavor and acts as a natural preservative"
